# Riverpod Conventions

## Always Use Code Generation

Every provider must use the `@riverpod` annotation from `riverpod_annotation`.
Do not use `Provider(...)`, `StateProvider(...)`, etc. directly — always use
the code-gen equivalents (`@riverpod` function for functional providers,
`@riverpod class` extending `_$NotifierName` for notifiers).

```dart
// Correct: code-gen provider
@riverpod
Future<List<Vm>> allVms(Ref ref) async {
  final api = ref.watch(apiClientProvider);
  return api.getAllVms();
}

// Wrong: manual provider — do not use
final allVmsProvider = FutureProvider<List<Vm>>((ref) async { ... });
```

## ref.watch vs ref.read for selectedServerProvider

In `apiClientProvider`, always use `ref.watch` (never `ref.read`) for
`selectedServerProvider`. This is critical: it ensures that when the user
switches servers, `apiClientProvider` is rebuilt and all downstream API
providers are invalidated automatically.

```dart
@riverpod
ProxmoxApiClient apiClient(Ref ref) {
  final server = ref.watch(selectedServerProvider); // watch — not read
  return ProxmoxApiClient(server: server);
}
```

If `ref.read` is used instead, server-switching will silently use stale data.

## AsyncNotifier for Async State

Use `AsyncNotifier` (via `@riverpod class ... extends _$...`) for state that
loads async data on `build()`. Use a plain `@riverpod` function (FutureProvider)
for read-only async data with no mutations.

```dart
@riverpod
class VmListNotifier extends _$VmListNotifier {
  @override
  Future<List<Vm>> build() => ref.watch(vmRepositoryProvider).getAllVms();

  Future<void> refresh() => ref.invalidateSelf();
}
```

## Provider File Placement

All provider files must live under `features/*/providers/` or
`shared/providers/`. Never define providers in screen files or repository files.

## Handling AsyncValue in the UI

Never expose raw `AsyncValue` to child widgets. Always handle all three states
(loading, error, data) in the screen or top-level widget, then pass typed data
to children:

```dart
// Correct
final vmsAsync = ref.watch(allVmsProvider);
return vmsAsync.when(
  loading: () => const LoadingShimmer(),
  error: (e, _) => ErrorView(message: e.toString(), onRetry: () => ref.invalidate(allVmsProvider)),
  data: (vms) => VmList(vms: vms),
);

// Wrong — never pass AsyncValue<List<Vm>> to a child widget
```
